  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "In this paper, a document is first split into sentences which are then grouped into chunks.",
    "We evaluate three chunking strategies, hereafter referred to as \"chunkers.\"",
    "Fixed-size Chunker This is our baseline chunker that splits a document sequentially into fixed-size chunks, based on a predefined or user-specified number of sentences per chunk.",
    "Although this approach is simple and computationally efficient, it may separate contextually related sentences, leading to potential degradation in retrieval quality (Lewis et al., 2020; Finardi et al., 2024; Gao et al., 2023).",
    "To alleviate this, we use overlapping sentences between consecutive chunks, a common practice to maintain some degree of contextual continuity."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Although this approach is simple and computationally efficient, it may separate contextually related sentences, leading to potential degradation in retrieval quality (Lewis et al., 2020; Finardi et al., 2024; Gao et al., 2023)."
